medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Born by cesarean section in the 35th week of gestation due to fetal distress. Twin A had a 1-cm phallus with chordee and penoscrotal hypospadias, while Twin B had a 0.5-cm phallus with perineal hypospadias and no palpable gonad on the right.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Pregnancy complicated by diabetes, depression, and polytrauma in the first month. The mother had two previous gestations.
medical_history.family_history: Family history unremarkable except for a maternal aunt with primary amenorrhea.
